'''David Griman''' (born [[1967-03-10]] in [[Los Teques]]) is a former [[Venezuela]]n professional [[Boxing|boxer]]. He is a former [[World Boxing Association]] (WBA) [[flyweight]] (112 [[pound (mass)|lb]]) champion.

== Amateur highlights ==
*1986 flyweight Bronze Medalist at the Goodwill Games in Moscow. Results were:
**Defeated [[Lernik Papyan]] (Soviet Union) points
**Lost to [[Arthur Johnson]] (United States) points
*1986 flyweight runner-up at World Championships in Reno, United States. Lost to [[Pedro Reyes]] of Cuba on points in the final
*1987 flyweight Silver Medalist at Pan-American Games
*Represented Venezuela as a Flyweight at 1988 Seoul [[Olympic Games]]. Result was:
**Lost to [[Serafim Todorov]] (Bulgaria) points

== Professional career ==
Griman turned professional in 1989 and captured the WBA flyweight title in 1992 with a decision win over [[Aquiles Guzman]]. He defended it twice before losing to [[Saen Sor Ploenchit]] by [[split decision]] in 1994. 

